# Trivy SCA suppressions — documented VEX (Vulnerability Exploitability eXchange) register.
#
# Read by the `SCA · Trivy (deps + license)` gate in .github/workflows/security-scan.yml,
# which scans the filesystem from the repo root (scan-ref ".", severity CRITICAL,
# --ignore-unfixed). Each CVE below is CRITICAL but assessed not_affected for MolTrace's
# real deployment: the vulnerable code is not in the execute path. Reachability for every
# entry was confirmed by code inspection AND an independent adversarial re-check (each
# returned "no reachable path found"). Bump-vs-suppress was decided per CVE; the
# jupyter-server CVE was instead FIXED by bumping to 2.20.0 (see moltrace_backend/pyproject.toml
# [tool.uv] constraint-dependencies) and is deliberately NOT listed here.
#
# Re-evaluate these whenever the relevant component moves into a deployed install path.

# --- torch (moltrace_backend/nmrnet_service/requirements.txt) ---
# CVE-2025-32434 — torch.load RCE via an untrusted checkpoint (fixed in torch 2.6.0).
# Status: not_affected. Justification: vulnerable_code_not_in_execute_path.
#   * torch is NOT a dependency of the MolTrace backend (absent from pyproject.toml; the
#     backend is deliberately torch-free). It is pinned only in nmrnet_service/, an
#     unfinished GPU-inference scaffold: nmrnet_service/app.py _load_model()/_run_inference()
#     raise NotImplementedError and the only torch.load there is a commented-out example.
#   * No Dockerfile/render/CI config references nmrnet_service — it is not wired into any deploy.
#   * The in-backend torch.load sites (nmrnet_wrapper.py, nus/reconstruct.py) are guarded by an
#     `import torch` that fails first in prod, and each is immediately followed by raising
#     *Unavailable() (unfilled integration stubs).
#   * The checkpoint path is operator-pinned (MOLTRACE_NMRNET_WEIGHTS / a Zenodo URL with
#     optional SHA-256 verification), never a user upload; the request contract carries only
#     molecular geometry / SMILES, never a checkpoint file.
#   * Bumping is not viable without breakage: the prebuilt Uni-Core wheel is compiled for
#     cu116/torch1.12/py3.8; torch 2.6 drops cu116, requires py>=3.9, and changes the ATen ABI.
#   Re-evaluate (drop this and bump to torch>=2.6.0 with a rebuilt Uni-Core wheel) once
#   nmrnet_service is actually implemented and wired into a deployment.
CVE-2025-32434

# --- mlflow (moltrace_backend/pyproject.toml [project.optional-dependencies] infra; uv.lock) ---
# Status: not_affected for all six. Justification: vulnerable_code_not_in_execute_path.
#   * mlflow is declared ONLY in the optional `infra` extra and present in uv.lock solely
#     because uv locks all optional groups (marker extra=='infra'). It is intentionally never
#     installed: prod deploy is `uv sync --no-dev --extra fid`; CI is `--extra fid --extra dev`.
#   * MolTrace uses mlflow ONLY as a client logging adapter (src/moltrace/spectroscopy/infra/
#     tracking.py): set_tracking_uri/start_run/log_params/log_metrics/log_artifact to a local
#     file store. It never starts a tracking server, never serves models, never sets
#     enable_mlserver, and never instantiates MlflowClient (verified by grep across src/).
#   * CVE-2026-0545 (GHSA-7qhf-v65m-g5f3, CVSS 9.1) is the /ajax-api/3.0/jobs/* job endpoints
#     bypassing the basic-auth app when MLFLOW_SERVER_ENABLE_JOB_EXECUTION + an allowlisted job
#     are enabled — same server surface; no patched mlflow version exists yet.
#   * CVE-2026-2651 (fixed in mlflow 3.11.0rc1) is arbitrary code execution via the tracking
#     server's unauthorized multipart artifact-upload endpoint — again a SERVER surface. MolTrace's
#     client `log_artifact` writes to the local file:// store; it never uploads to, nor runs, a
#     tracking server. A fix exists, but a bump is not warranted while infra stays un-deployed: the
#     only fix is a major-version jump (2.x -> 3.x) to a currently pre-release line, for a package
#     that is never installed.
#   * All six CVEs require running mlflow's SERVER / model-SERVING components, which MolTrace
#     does not run.
#   Re-evaluate if MolTrace ever ships the `infra` extra in a deploy target or runs an mlflow
#   server/serving process — then bump to a patched mlflow (3.11.x covers CVE-2026-2651; some
#   others, e.g. CVE-2026-0545, still had no fix as of 2026-06-25).
CVE-2025-15036
CVE-2025-15379
CVE-2026-0596
CVE-2026-2635
CVE-2026-0545
CVE-2026-2651
